WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.320
I'm a general practitioner,
what's here I think you call a family physician.

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:09.360
I work within the NHS,
I've been doing this work for about ten years.

00:00:11.160 --> 00:00:14.560
If I could just pick up on a few
of Dr. Patrick's remarks

00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:24.160
about the type of patients we see
and who may benefit from complementary therapies.

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:29.960
The most difficult part of my work
is dealing with people with chronic illnesses,

00:00:31.040 --> 00:00:37.440
chronic distress whether it comes
from physical, psychological or social problems.

00:00:38.440 --> 00:00:42.440
Those are the patients
that really pose the difficulties.

00:00:42.440 --> 00:00:45.520
And those are the people that maybe&nbsp;

00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:54.320
are going to benefit most&nbsp;
from non-drug approaches.

00:00:54.320 --> 00:00:58.640
I've been interested in Sahaja Yoga
myself for about twenty years.

00:00:59.160 --> 00:01:06.720
I'm mainly going to be talking about
the research being carried out into Sahaja Yoga.

00:01:06.720 --> 00:01:11.000
But if you look through the literature
about yoga and meditation in general,

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:16.080
it's surprising how many illnesses,
how many different conditions you'll find

00:01:16.880 --> 00:01:19.480
where there are published studies.

00:01:19.480 --> 00:01:25.160
Just to run through a partial list,
there's hypertension, coronary artery disease,

00:01:25.160 --> 00:01:32.040
heart failure, asthma, osteoarthritis,
diabetes, epilepsy, migraine,

00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:37.320
anxiety, depression, stress,
chemical dependency

00:01:37.320 --> 00:01:40.640
and obsessive-compulsive disorder.

00:01:41.600 --> 00:01:47.800
In the US, you now have more patients
consulting complementary practitioners

00:01:47.800 --> 00:01:58.080
than consulting conventional doctors,
and we're not far behind in Britain.

00:01:58.840 --> 00:02:01.640
I myself have been interested
in Sahaja Yoga for twenty years

00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:06.920
and there are quite a number of doctors
who have been practising for that length of time.

00:02:06.920 --> 00:02:15.000
When I first came in, I was quite sceptical
about the benefits to health, to myself.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:22.120
But what really intrigued me
were my own experiences.

00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:27.680
If I could have the first slide, please?

00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:34.120
This is a diagrammatic representation
of what we call the subtle system.

00:02:34.120 --> 00:02:39.720
This is mainly what Shri Mataji
is going to talk about when she arrives.

00:02:39.720 --> 00:02:46.320
So I won't discuss it in any detail,
but I myself have experiences

00:02:46.320 --> 00:02:49.840
which relate to this system.

00:02:49.840 --> 00:02:52.800
The other thing which struck me
and various colleagues

00:02:52.800 --> 00:02:58.480
was how many people practising yoga
would come up to us without any prompting

00:02:58.480 --> 00:03:01.800
and say that their health
had benefited in various ways.

00:03:01.800 --> 00:03:06.200
So I decided to undertake
a questionnaire survey.

00:03:06.200 --> 00:03:09.600
I distributed questionnaires
amongst the practitioners,

00:03:09.600 --> 00:03:19.120
asking them to report whether
they felt their health had improved or not.

00:03:19.120 --> 00:03:22.600
And these are the results.

00:03:22.600 --> 00:03:30.120
Basically, those people with health index
4 or 5 reported their health had improved.

00:03:30.120 --> 00:03:35.080
The message of this slide is that in general,
the longer people had been practising,

00:03:35.080 --> 00:03:40.240
the more they felt
their health had improved.

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:48.440
The sorts of illnesses people described
were not major life-threatening conditions,

00:03:48.440 --> 00:04:06.000
but things like chronic musculoskeletal problems,
asthma, minor psychological illnesses.

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:07.680
So that's the first study.

00:04:07.680 --> 00:04:09.400
I'm now going to move on to talk about&nbsp;

00:04:09.400 --> 00:04:14.640
some research carried out at&nbsp;
the University of New Delhi.

00:04:14.640 --> 00:04:18.560
Over a number of years under the auspices
of Professor Rai,

00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:25.240
who, as Dr. Katchek already mentioned,
was here two years ago and gave a lecture.

00:04:25.240 --> 00:04:28.920
The first part of this research project
was to look at the physiological effects

00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:35.080
of Sahaja Yoga meditation.

00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:40.200
The message of this slide is that
as people meditate,

00:04:40.200 --> 00:04:45.040
galvanic skin resistance increases.

00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:54.520
And as people learn Sahaja Yoga
over the course of 16 weeks,

00:04:54.520 --> 00:04:59.560
the baseline also increases.

00:05:03.200 --> 00:05:16.760
Blood lactic acid concentrations decrease.
Urinary VMA decreases.

00:05:16.760 --> 00:05:25.680
Systolic blood pressure decreases.

00:05:27.120 --> 00:05:32.560
To summarise the physiology, we can say
it's all consistent with the reduction

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:35.880
in sympathetic nervous activity.

00:05:35.880 --> 00:05:40.920
Other observations were an increase
in alpha activity on the EEG

00:05:40.920 --> 00:05:46.680
and in a separate study at McMaster University,
it was shown that beta endorphins rise

00:05:46.680 --> 00:05:51.640
whilst people are practising Sahaja Yoga.

00:05:51.640 --> 00:05:56.920
Moving on now to a number of clinical studies.
First is hypertension.

00:05:56.920 --> 00:06:02.680
This is a study in which 15 hypertensive patients
were followed up for 16 weeks.

00:06:04.640 --> 00:06:14.200
The diastolic blood pressure fell
from an average of just over 109 to 86.

00:06:15.320 --> 00:06:21.480
And the systolic blood pressure fell
from about 170 to 135.

00:06:21.480 --> 00:06:27.920
This was despite a reduction in medication
amongst the Sahaja Yoga group.

00:06:27.920 --> 00:06:31.680
So essentially, a group
of uncontrolled hypertensives

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:37.920
where their control was improved
and yet their medication was reduced.

00:06:37.920 --> 00:06:43.120
In asthma, 9 patients again
followed up for 16 weeks.

00:06:43.120 --> 00:06:48.360
This slide shows a significant improvement
in lung function

00:06:48.360 --> 00:06:54.080
and there was also a reduction
in the number of acute asthma attacks.

00:06:54.080 --> 00:06:59.400
Again, in most cases there was a reduction
in the medication taken.

00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:07.440
The third study was on epilepsy.
10 patients followed up for 6 months.

00:07:07.440 --> 00:07:14.800
Over that 6 months, the average frequency
of attacks was reduced from over 4

00:07:15.360 --> 00:07:17.760
to less than 1 attack a month.

00:07:17.760 --> 00:07:29.320
And 3 patients had stopped
having attacks altogether.

00:07:31.360 --> 00:07:40.680
So those were all fairly small
and fairly short studies done in India.

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:44.840
They've all been replicated in Australia.

00:07:44.840 --> 00:07:49.640
There's currently a research programme
underway at the University of New South Wales,

00:07:49.640 --> 00:07:58.880
and they are moving on to do
larger and more rigorous studies.

00:07:58.880 --> 00:08:01.440
So that is my presentation.

00:08:02.600 --> 00:08:07.080
I'm going to ask Dr. Ashish Pradhan to come.

00:08:07.080 --> 00:08:09.560
He is a clinical pharmacologist&nbsp;

00:08:09.560 --> 00:08:13.040
currently working for Bristol&nbsp;
Myers Squibb in Montreal,

00:08:13.040 --> 00:08:19.800
where he's the project manager
of health outcomes and economic evaluation.

00:08:21.080 --> 00:08:59.200
So Dr. Pradhan.

00:09:56.560 --> 00:09:57.560
---

00:09:57.560 --> 00:10:36.520
A very succinct and brief presentation&nbsp;

00:10:36.520 --> 00:10:40.320
regarding the studies conducted&nbsp;
so far in Sahaja Yoga.

00:10:40.320 --> 00:10:44.400
What we are going to try to do
over the next 10 minutes or so

00:10:44.400 --> 00:10:50.240
is to take a very quick overview
of the subtle system

00:10:50.240 --> 00:10:52.480
to which he alluded,&nbsp;

00:10:52.480 --> 00:10:56.680
and about which you shall&nbsp;
be hearing in further detail

00:11:01.400 --> 00:11:03.800
from Shri Mataji herself.

00:11:04.560 --> 00:11:10.040
As a background to what we are going to see
and what you are going to hear from her,

00:11:10.040 --> 00:11:16.200
it would be useful to know
what the subtle system is about

00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:20.080
and what kind of role it plays in our body.

00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:25.160
And what kind of effect it would have
on the health outcomes

00:11:25.160 --> 00:11:28.240
vis-à-vis the model of Sahaja Yoga.

00:11:28.240 --> 00:11:35.920
We are also going to see very briefly
some epidemiological evidence

00:11:35.920 --> 00:11:39.000
regarding some of the hypotheses.

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:45.880
What we can at the present moment regard
as hypotheses, regarding the aetiology

00:11:45.880 --> 00:11:49.280
of certain things.

00:11:49.280 --> 00:11:59.440
The causal relationship, as we would do
in more rigorously controlled studies,

00:11:59.440 --> 00:12:04.200
is certainly an issue where you deal with
the whole paradigm of meditation

00:12:04.200 --> 00:12:07.000
and its effects on health.

00:12:07.600 --> 00:12:12.760
What we have tried to do here
is based on what Shri Mataji has been saying

00:12:12.760 --> 00:12:15.480
for the past 30 years.

00:12:15.480 --> 00:12:18.360
We have tried to get from the available&nbsp;

00:12:18.360 --> 00:12:23.680
medical literature whatever&nbsp;
evidence may be available

00:12:23.680 --> 00:12:31.120
to see if we can find evidence
that conforms to those hypotheses

00:12:31.120 --> 00:12:36.000
that Shri Mataji has been talking about
for the past almost three decades.

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:38.880
So we shall come to that
in the latter half of the presentation.

00:12:42.800 --> 00:12:44.640
This is the overview of the presentation.

00:12:44.640 --> 00:12:48.600
We shall be taking a look
at the subtle system.

00:12:48.600 --> 00:12:57.240
We shall be looking at what is the aetiology
of disease according to the model of Sahaja Yoga.

00:12:57.240 --> 00:13:00.280
Then we shall be looking
at the epidemiological evidence

00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:05.840
and we shall be concluding
with some key messages.

00:13:05.840 --> 00:13:11.360
The subtle system is composed
of what are called in Sanskrit as nadis,

00:13:11.360 --> 00:13:15.880
or channels of energy,
and they correspond basically

00:13:15.880 --> 00:13:20.200
with the autonomic nervous system.

00:13:20.200 --> 00:13:26.480
Then we have the centres
which are called as chakras

00:13:26.480 --> 00:13:32.560
and they correspond
with the nervous plexuses.

00:13:32.560 --> 00:13:38.280
Finally, we have within each one of us,
situated at the base of the spine,

00:13:38.280 --> 00:13:44.960
the triangular bone, a residual dormant energy
which is called as the Kundalini energy.

00:13:44.960 --> 00:13:50.080
So for the purposes of introduction,
these are the three most important components

00:13:50.080 --> 00:13:54.480
that we have to bear in mind.

00:13:54.480 --> 00:13:58.840
The nadis are predominantly three in number.

00:13:58.840 --> 00:14:02.080
On the right side we have
what is called as the Ida Nadi,

00:14:02.080 --> 00:14:05.040
and this side governs our emotions&nbsp;

00:14:05.040 --> 00:14:11.160
and it corresponds to the right&nbsp;
sympathetic nervous system.

00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:15.120
Then we have the Pingala Nadi&nbsp;

00:14:17.680 --> 00:14:20.520
which corresponds to the right&nbsp;
sympathetic nervous system

00:14:22.040 --> 00:14:26.680
and that part governs our actions.

00:14:26.680 --> 00:14:29.920
And then finally we have
the Susumna Nadi

00:14:32.160 --> 00:14:34.880
which corresponds to the parasympathetic
nervous system

00:14:34.880 --> 00:14:41.120
and this governs our evolution.

00:14:41.120 --> 00:14:45.240
The chakras are predominantly seven in number;
we shall quickly run through them.

00:14:45.240 --> 00:14:48.480
At the bottom we have
what is called as the Mooladhara Chakra

00:14:48.480 --> 00:14:49.112
which corresponds to the coccygeal plexus.

00:14:49.112 --> 00:14:56.400
We have the Swadisthana Chakra
which corresponds with the aortic plexus.

00:14:56.400 --> 00:15:01.000
We have the Manipura Chakra
which corresponds with the celiac plexus.

00:15:01.000 --> 00:15:06.000
We have the Anahata Chakra
which corresponds with the cardiac plexus.

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:10.320
We have the Vishuddhi Chakra
which corresponds with the cervical plexus.

00:15:10.320 --> 00:15:13.440
The Agnya which corresponds
with the optic chiasma

00:15:13.440 --> 00:15:15.680
and the Sahasrara Chakra&nbsp;

00:15:15.680 --> 00:15:23.240
which corresponds predominantly&nbsp;
with the limbic system.

00:15:23.240 --> 00:15:27.920
The Kundalini is a dormant residual energy

00:15:27.920 --> 00:15:33.520
and it is the instrument of our Self-realization
through its ascension

00:15:33.520 --> 00:15:38.400
and establishment of union, or yoga.

00:15:38.400 --> 00:15:43.360
Yoga, as Shri Mataji has said,
is basically the union.

00:15:43.360 --> 00:15:49.200
So when the union takes place,
we say that the real yoga has occurred.

00:15:49.200 --> 00:15:58.680
In other words, yoga in the classical sense
has got nothing to do with physical postures

00:15:58.680 --> 00:16:01.400
or those kinds of calisthenics.

00:16:01.400 --> 00:16:09.280
But it is an innate internal happening —
it is basically the occurrence of the union.

00:16:09.280 --> 00:16:17.480
And the Kundalini energy is the instrument
through which this union can take place.

00:16:17.480 --> 00:16:19.840
So what is Self-realization?

00:16:19.840 --> 00:16:28.240
It is the upward ascent of the Kundalini energy
through the certain centres

00:16:28.240 --> 00:16:34.920
and establishment of the union
through the All-pervading Divine Power.

00:16:34.920 --> 00:16:40.440
It manifests — and this is extremely important —
it manifests as the flow of a cool breeze,

00:16:40.440 --> 00:16:46.080
which in Sahaja Yoga we call vibrations,
from the palms of the hands

00:16:46.080 --> 00:16:52.240
and from the top of the head.

00:16:52.240 --> 00:16:57.600
Let us take a look at what is
the aetiology of disease in Sahaja Yoga.

00:16:57.600 --> 00:17:01.920
But basically we have to define
what is a health state,

00:17:01.920 --> 00:17:05.520
what is positive health
according to Sahaja Yoga.

00:17:05.520 --> 00:17:10.200
It can simply be characterised
with three conditions:

00:17:10.200 --> 00:17:16.320
no blockages on the chakras
or on those energy centres,

00:17:16.320 --> 00:17:22.560
a harmonious and steady flow of the cool breeze
through the palms of your hands

00:17:22.560 --> 00:17:24.520
and from the top of the head,

00:17:24.520 --> 00:17:30.720
and a state of complete balance
within the subtle system.

00:17:30.720 --> 00:17:39.720
When the internal system within us,
if all the elements within that system

00:17:39.720 --> 00:17:46.280
are in perfect harmony, in perfect balance,
then we say that that is positive health.

00:17:46.280 --> 00:17:54.840
So obviously disease would be
a disturbance in this state of balance.

00:17:54.840 --> 00:17:58.400
Primarily, the cause of disease
according to Sahaja Yoga

00:17:58.400 --> 00:18:03.800
is an imbalance in the subtle system,
secondary to blockages in the chakra.

00:18:03.800 --> 00:18:13.280
This is a very simplistic mechanistic model
of understanding disease through Sahaja Yoga.

00:18:13.280 --> 00:18:18.000
Now if we have to understand
what is the causal relationship

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:24.160
between imbalances
and disease manifestation,

00:18:29.160 --> 00:18:35.440
we have to look at just some of the hypotheses
that Shri Mataji has been saying over the years.

00:18:35.440 --> 00:18:39.720
We are going to examine just three
of those hypotheses

00:18:39.720 --> 00:18:43.560
for which we have found
kind of evidence in the literature.

00:18:43.560 --> 00:18:47.240
These are not studies
that Sahaja Yoga has conducted.

00:18:53.720 --> 00:18:56.600
These are studies which are available
in the literature

00:18:56.600 --> 00:19:02.720
and they were retrieved through the search
of medical databases like Medline.

00:19:02.720 --> 00:19:12.080
So basically the first hypothesis
is excessive and inappropriate activity

00:19:12.080 --> 00:19:19.480
of the right sympathetic nervous system,
your Pingala Nadi on the right-hand side,

00:19:19.480 --> 00:19:24.760
leads to a direct effect
on the heart centre.

00:19:33.720 --> 00:19:38.600
When we say excessive and inappropriate,
it means that if a person

00:19:38.600 --> 00:19:42.800
is more likely by nature
to get angry pretty quickly,

00:19:42.800 --> 00:19:48.680
or has increased hostility within him,
or has a kind of a domineering nature,

00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:51.520
because the right side
governs our actions.

00:19:51.520 --> 00:19:57.720
Yes, we need to perform our actions.
But actions have to be tempered with compassion,

00:19:57.720 --> 00:20:01.560
with the right quantum of emotional input.

00:20:01.560 --> 00:20:05.800
Otherwise, it tends to go
into a system of imbalance.

00:20:07.120 --> 00:20:11.040
Due to the constraints of time
we cannot go into too many details,

00:20:11.040 --> 00:20:17.400
but this is a simplistic notion
of what excessive right-side activity would mean

00:20:17.400 --> 00:20:20.080
and its effect on the heart centre.

00:20:20.080 --> 00:20:27.160
Bearing that in mind, the first study
was the ARIC study published by Williams et al

00:20:27.160 --> 00:20:29.360
in Circulation just a couple of weeks ago.

00:20:29.360 --> 00:20:33.440
The investigators were from Duke University
and from Johns Hopkins University.

00:20:34.520 --> 00:20:40.040
The design was a prospective study
of 13,000 individuals over five years

00:20:40.040 --> 00:20:47.760
for the association between anger trait
and the risk of cardiovascular events.

00:20:49.320 --> 00:20:54.800
So called soft events were incidents of angina,
non-fatal myocardial infarction,

00:20:54.800 --> 00:21:01.960
as compared to heart events
like acute MI and coronary heart disease.

00:21:01.960 --> 00:21:09.480
Basically the patients filled out a questionnaire
identifying whether they had an anger trait,

00:21:09.480 --> 00:21:13.240
whether they were more likely
to get angry relative to some other people.

00:21:18.960 --> 00:21:21.800
This was part of the atherosclerosis risk&nbsp;

00:21:21.800 --> 00:21:27.480
in community study done&nbsp;
all over the United States.

00:21:27.480 --> 00:21:53.080
The results — if we look at the odds ratios
for high versus low anger —

00:21:53.080 --> 00:22:04.920
it is 2.2 and the 95% confidence interval
ranges from 1.36 to 3.5,

00:22:04.920 --> 00:22:10.600
which means if you are a person
who gets angry fast,

00:22:12.280 --> 00:22:18.160
your chance of getting a fatal MI
or a cardiac event

00:22:18.160 --> 00:22:20.760
is between 1 to 3 times&nbsp;

00:22:20.760 --> 00:22:26.480
as compared to someone who&nbsp;
does not have that trait.

00:22:26.480 --> 00:22:33.720
For heart events in fact it was 2.6
with a confidence interval of 1.4 to 4.9.

00:22:33.720 --> 00:22:37.680
The second study was done in Portugal
by Coelho and colleagues

00:22:37.680 --> 00:22:41.960
and was published in the Journal
of Cardiovascular Risk last year.

00:22:41.960 --> 00:22:46.200
It was a case-controlled study
where cases of acute myocardial infarction

00:22:46.200 --> 00:22:49.160
were compared to controls.

00:22:51.600 --> 00:22:57.000
Cases of AMI versus controls,
type A behaviour was found

00:22:57.000 --> 00:23:01.080
to be a significant predictor
of acute myocardial infarction,

00:23:01.080 --> 00:23:02.760
and it was also found&nbsp;

00:23:02.760 --> 00:23:05.800
that they had significantly&nbsp;
more depressive symptoms.

00:23:06.560 --> 00:23:13.760
What this suggests is that within
a psychosocial construct of an individual

00:23:13.760 --> 00:23:16.640
there was some kind of an imbalance,

00:23:16.640 --> 00:23:23.640
and anger is an emotion predominantly
controlled by the Agnya Chakra

00:23:24.480 --> 00:23:31.520
which, as we said in the hypothesis,
indirectly affects your heart.

00:23:31.520 --> 00:23:39.400
Further evidence comes from this American study
published in the American Journal of Epidemiology.

00:23:43.200 --> 00:23:48.480
It was a prospective cohort study,
2,200 men over a 9-year period.

00:23:48.480 --> 00:23:55.080
The odds ratios: men with hostility scores
in the top quartile

00:23:55.080 --> 00:24:03.120
had an all-cause mortality of 2.3
with a 95% interval of 1.4 to 3.5.

00:24:03.120 --> 00:24:08.840
Cardiovascular mortality was 2.7
with a CI of 1 to 5.

00:24:08.840 --> 00:24:14.960
The last study in this category
was published in Psychosomatic Medicine

00:24:14.960 --> 00:24:19.000
by Gallagher and colleagues.

00:24:19.000 --> 00:24:21.560
This was a random sample cohort study

00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:31.640
and the predictive value of a low anger-out score
for ischaemic heart disease events was 1.7.

00:24:31.640 --> 00:24:35.280
Again, it was a statistically significant outcome.

00:24:35.280 --> 00:24:39.680
In this study patients had to fill in questions:&nbsp;

00:24:39.680 --> 00:24:44.120
anger in, anger out, do I&nbsp;
express myself when angry.

00:24:45.640 --> 00:24:55.880
So basically these studies show us
that out there in the world of epidemiology

00:24:55.880 --> 00:25:04.600
we are beginning to find evidence
which might lend support to the thesis

00:25:04.600 --> 00:25:11.440
that imbalance within us,
especially mediated through anger or hostility,

00:25:11.440 --> 00:25:14.680
may have deleterious effects on cardiac events.

00:25:15.200 --> 00:25:22.480
All these studies were done adjusting
for traditional cardiovascular risk factors

00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:27.280
like smoking, hypertension,
obesity and diabetes.

00:25:28.480 --> 00:25:35.000
So in a multiple regression model,
even if you adjust for those factors,

00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:41.640
factors like anger and hostility
stand out as independent risk factors

00:25:41.640 --> 00:25:45.480
for cardiovascular disease.

00:25:45.480 --> 00:25:51.360
The second is anxiety or insecurity
predisposing women to an increased risk

00:25:51.360 --> 00:25:52.260
of breast cancer.

00:25:52.260 --> 00:25:56.320
Shri Mataji has been talking about this
for a number of years.

00:25:57.160 --> 00:26:00.920
What we found in one study
published in the Journal of Cancer,

00:26:01.760 --> 00:26:05.560
done in the United Kingdom
by Walter and Collins.

00:26:05.560 --> 00:26:10.760
This was a randomised prospective study
of relaxation training

00:26:11.680 --> 00:26:14.280
on response to primary chemotherapy.

00:26:14.280 --> 00:26:18.960
This is not incidence of breast cancer.
These are breast cancer patients

00:26:18.960 --> 00:26:22.720
who have been followed up
over a certain period of time.

00:26:22.720 --> 00:26:26.440
The primary outcome variable is&nbsp;

00:26:26.440 --> 00:26:30.640
whether or not they are&nbsp;
responding to breast cancer.

00:26:30.640 --> 00:26:33.080
The results are quite fascinating.

00:26:33.080 --> 00:26:37.040
The HADS score — the hospital anxiety
and depression score —

00:26:37.040 --> 00:26:40.600
both depression and anxiety were significant&nbsp;

00:26:40.600 --> 00:26:43.240
independent predictors of&nbsp;
response to chemotherapy.

00:26:44.040 --> 00:26:48.600
Women who had very high scores
of anxiety and depression

00:26:48.600 --> 00:26:57.600
had a higher likelihood of having recurrence,
or failing to respond adequately to chemotherapy.

00:26:59.160 --> 00:27:05.880
The last hypothesis is
that, as Shri Mataji explains,

00:27:05.880 --> 00:27:17.320
after marriage the husband and wife
complement each other's state of health.

00:27:17.320 --> 00:27:24.800
So if the wife is having some kind of problems,
it does reflect in the husband's health

00:27:24.800 --> 00:27:25.920
and vice versa.

00:27:35.440 --> 00:27:37.840
One would say why do you need a study
to prove that?

00:27:37.840 --> 00:27:44.000
But this study was carried out
at the University of Utah

00:27:44.000 --> 00:27:50.040
under experimental conditions
by Brown et al.

00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:53.360
It was a randomised controlled trial
of 45 married husbands

00:27:54.600 --> 00:27:58.960
to assess whether the perception
of spousal dominance

00:27:58.960 --> 00:28:03.600
can predict blood pressure reactivity.

00:28:03.600 --> 00:28:06.640
The primary outcome was
systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

00:28:08.400 --> 00:28:13.600
The results stated that subjects
interacting with the spouse perceived as dominant

00:28:13.600 --> 00:28:17.120
were associated with having
a higher blood pressure.

00:28:22.080 --> 00:28:24.280
So what are the key messages?

00:28:24.280 --> 00:28:26.320
Psychosocial factors are emerging&nbsp;

00:28:26.320 --> 00:28:31.440
as significant independent&nbsp;
risk factors of disease.

00:28:31.440 --> 00:28:37.560
Sahaja Yoga presents an excellent model
for explaining the role of these risk factors

00:28:37.560 --> 00:28:42.480
in terms of a possible aetiological role.

00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:50.040
For example, when we say that there is
some kind of an internal imbalance.

00:28:50.040 --> 00:28:53.920
Sahaja Yoga therefore affords&nbsp;
a critical alternative&nbsp;

00:28:53.920 --> 00:28:56.400
for management of these diseases

00:28:56.400 --> 00:29:02.800
through a simple and effortless programme
of correcting these internal imbalances.

00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:07.840
How that happens is something&nbsp;
that you will find out&nbsp;

00:29:07.840 --> 00:29:10.680
when Shri Mataji is here&nbsp;
and she will speak to you.

00:29:11.320 --> 00:29:19.200
What we want to say is that there is this kind
of evidence out there,

00:29:19.200 --> 00:29:24.400
and though we know that these relationships
might exist between these risk factors

00:29:24.400 --> 00:29:27.600
and heart outcomes,
how do you cure?

00:29:27.600 --> 00:29:34.400
There is no pill that's available,
there is no procedure you can undergo

00:29:34.400 --> 00:29:38.640
in order to have an effect
on these kinds of outcomes.

00:29:38.640 --> 00:29:42.960
It basically calls for setting right
your internal imbalances

00:29:42.960 --> 00:29:46.480
and maintaining a state
of positive spiritual health,

00:29:46.480 --> 00:29:50.440
which then has an absolutely salutary effect
on the physical health.

00:29:50.440 --> 00:29:52.200
And this is where Sahaja Yoga can help.

00:29:53.640 --> 00:29:56.880
Our next speaker is Dr. Brian Wells.

00:29:56.880 --> 00:30:05.440
He is a consultant psychiatrist
who specialises in addictive medicine.

00:30:05.440 --> 00:30:10.320
He is based in central London
and has an international private practice.

00:30:10.320 --> 00:30:27.240
He has lectured at many international conferences.
Dr. Brian Wells, thank you.

00:30:36.040 --> 00:30:37.040
---

00:30:37.040 --> 00:30:43.520
Good evening, my name is Brian Wells
as Dr. Pradhan mentioned.

00:30:43.520 --> 00:30:46.360
I would like to thank Dr. George Patrick
very much indeed

00:30:46.360 --> 00:30:49.240
for allowing us the opportunity
to come here tonight,

00:30:49.240 --> 00:30:51.200
and also to thank you all very much
for coming.

00:30:52.000 --> 00:30:57.760
It's well past the working hours —
Dr. Spiro and I are operating on UK time

00:30:57.760 --> 00:31:02.160
which is well past working hours.
Congratulations for coming.

00:31:02.160 --> 00:31:06.080
I know that you are all
eagerly awaiting the arrival of Shri Mataji

00:31:06.080 --> 00:31:06.920
and I can assure you,&nbsp;

00:31:06.920 --> 00:31:10.560
you are not going to be&nbsp;
disappointed when she comes.

00:31:10.560 --> 00:31:15.440
We have heard a fair bit about some
of the science around Sahaja Yoga

00:31:15.440 --> 00:31:19.360
and some may be feeling
that this is still very rudimentary.

00:31:19.360 --> 00:31:22.480
One of the reasons why we are eager
to present this evening

00:31:22.480 --> 00:31:28.400
is because we want to demonstrate
via properly methodologically sound research

00:31:28.400 --> 00:31:32.040
that the teachings of Shri Mataji
actually have a great deal to offer

00:31:32.040 --> 00:31:34.600
and that they are based
on a scientific basis,

00:31:34.600 --> 00:31:39.800
albeit presented in language
that some of us may not be familiar with.

00:31:39.800 --> 00:31:43.240
Some of the words like Kundalini,
chakras, nadis, etc.

00:31:43.240 --> 00:31:45.440
may not be familiar to all of us.

00:31:45.440 --> 00:31:49.680
They certainly weren't familiar to me
as an allopathic trained doctor

00:31:49.680 --> 00:31:55.000
who in the late 1970s
found himself having to become abstinent

00:31:55.000 --> 00:31:58.600
from alcohol and drugs
and go to 12-step meetings.

00:31:58.600 --> 00:32:01.000
I am sure you all know meetings
like Alcoholics Anonymous.

00:32:03.520 --> 00:32:12.040
And eventually in 1980 I managed
to get clean, get sober, go to AA,

00:32:12.040 --> 00:32:14.360
did my 90 meetings in 90 days in a row.

00:32:16.760 --> 00:32:24.320
As you may know the 12-step fellowships
have a leaning towards spirituality.

00:32:24.320 --> 00:32:27.560
They are not religious organisations.
There is quite a lot of talk

00:32:27.560 --> 00:32:29.400
about a power greater than oneself.

00:32:30.920 --> 00:32:38.600
As I was progressing through my own recovery
I found myself looking out for things

00:32:38.600 --> 00:32:41.160
that made spirituality more meaningful.

00:32:41.160 --> 00:32:45.800
I tried going back to religion,
I tried looking at different types of meditation,

00:32:45.800 --> 00:32:49.000
some of which I was very attracted to
and some of which I wasn't.

00:32:53.280 --> 00:32:59.480
Being someone interested in altered states
and chemical experiences,

00:33:00.280 --> 00:33:03.400
what I needed was something
that was experiential.

00:33:03.400 --> 00:33:09.720
I found if I sat in a lotus position,
for me, it didn't really do a whole lot.

00:33:09.720 --> 00:33:14.200
I was somebody who needed
spectacular experiences.

00:33:14.200 --> 00:33:18.080
And in 1982 I met an Indian doctor
who I was working with.

00:33:21.720 --> 00:33:23.800
I sat down and had lunch with him
and asked him what he had been doing.

00:33:23.800 --> 00:33:29.480
He said he had been travelling in India,
and he had met a meditation teacher.

00:33:29.480 --> 00:33:35.440
When he touched her feet,
he was plunged into this state of oneness

00:33:35.440 --> 00:33:37.840
and pure joy and pure knowledge.

00:33:37.840 --> 00:33:45.880
He felt this cold wind rushing through him
and he was in a state of pure joy.

00:33:45.880 --> 00:33:51.280
To an ex-drug using psychiatrist
looking for spiritual direction,

00:33:51.280 --> 00:33:53.280
it sounded highly interesting.

00:33:54.440 --> 00:33:59.837
I said, "Do you have to be Indian
in order to experience this?"

00:33:59.837 --> 00:34:03.880
So you certainly had to be Indian
in order to understand the terms he was using,

00:34:03.880 --> 00:34:05.640
like Kundalini and chakras.

00:34:07.040 --> 00:34:11.720
I have to say that in my own quest
I wasn't really a hippie.

00:34:11.720 --> 00:34:13.800
I never got to India.&nbsp;

00:34:13.800 --> 00:34:19.000
I would run out of money by&nbsp;
the time I got to the airport.

00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:24.160
I never quite did the Indian trip
which a lot of other people have done.

00:34:24.160 --> 00:34:27.240
But I found myself interested.
I liked this guy.

00:34:27.240 --> 00:34:29.440
He had something about him
that was appealing.

00:34:30.480 --> 00:34:34.280
And I was certainly interested to try this out.
I was trying out all sorts of other things.

00:34:34.280 --> 00:34:35.600
Why not this?

00:34:35.600 --> 00:34:38.840
He arranged for a couple of people
to come round to the hospital where I was.

00:34:38.840 --> 00:34:43.960
I had to be on duty that night.
They stood behind me.

00:34:43.960 --> 00:34:47.080
They had a photograph of Shri Mataji
and lit a candle.

00:34:48.000 --> 00:34:49.760
I looked at the photograph
and they stood behind me

00:34:49.760 --> 00:34:51.440
and seemed to wave their arms around&nbsp;

00:34:51.440 --> 00:34:54.720
and mutter things which I&nbsp;
now realise were Sanskrit.

00:34:57.240 --> 00:34:59.760
And I sat there waiting to be plunged&nbsp;

00:34:59.760 --> 00:35:06.040
into pure joy and knowledge&nbsp;
and oneness and ecstasy.

00:35:06.040 --> 00:35:07.760
It didn't quite happen.

00:35:07.760 --> 00:35:12.480
What I did feel was this cold experience
starting at the bottom of my legs,

00:35:12.480 --> 00:35:17.560
working its way up my legs
and stopping at the base of my spine.

00:35:17.560 --> 00:35:19.960
I was convinced that there was
a draft coming under the door.

00:35:19.960 --> 00:35:22.720
They said, "No, this is the sort of thing
that people experience."

00:35:22.720 --> 00:35:29.920
"People by and large do have some sort of
physical or physiological experience."

00:35:30.960 --> 00:35:33.600
They then said,
"Well, it started if you just meditate,

00:35:35.360 --> 00:35:36.880
just looking at the photograph,&nbsp;

00:35:36.880 --> 00:35:40.600
using a candle and achieving&nbsp;
a state of thoughtlessness.

00:35:40.600 --> 00:35:43.760
This will just happen for you.
You don't have to do anything."

00:35:47.440 --> 00:35:49.360
They left me with the photograph
and with the candle.

00:35:49.360 --> 00:35:51.760
I have to say I was a little disappointed.

00:35:51.760 --> 00:35:54.840
I was hoping for a thunderbolt
to come through the window

00:35:54.840 --> 00:35:57.760
and enlighten me
with oneness with God.

00:35:57.760 --> 00:35:59.320
That hadn't happened.

00:35:59.320 --> 00:36:04.880
But after they had gone,
I did know that something had happened.

00:36:04.880 --> 00:36:09.320
It was something that was totally free.
Nobody had asked me for any money.

00:36:09.320 --> 00:36:13.000
It was also something that I knew
in my heart was perfectly safe.

00:36:13.000 --> 00:36:14.880
This was not going to harm me.

00:36:14.880 --> 00:36:18.640
There was no question I had to wear funny clothes
or eat strange food

00:36:18.640 --> 00:36:21.960
or do anything
that I felt uncomfortable with.

00:36:21.960 --> 00:36:24.760
The people who had come around to see me,
they were working.

00:36:24.760 --> 00:36:26.000
They'd come around after work.&nbsp;

00:36:27.360 --> 00:36:30.840
One was a computer expert&nbsp;
and the other was his wife.

00:36:30.840 --> 00:36:34.800
There was nothing odd about them.
They didn't have weird beads on or anything.

00:36:35.320 --> 00:36:36.600
So I felt completely relaxed.

00:36:37.240 --> 00:36:40.400
After they'd gone, I became aware
of this —

00:36:40.400 --> 00:36:43.680
it was as though it was a bubble of air
that was following me around,

00:36:43.680 --> 00:36:47.960
sitting on top of my head
and following me around wherever I was.

00:36:47.960 --> 00:36:51.440
I was also aware that my visual perception
had changed slightly.

00:36:51.440 --> 00:36:54.520
I remember looking at the on-call room I was in.&nbsp;

00:36:54.520 --> 00:36:58.680
It had a white porcelain sink&nbsp;
with a bar of green soap.

00:36:58.680 --> 00:37:04.200
It slightly stood out.&nbsp;

00:37:04.200 --> 00:37:06.360
It was as though I'd taken&nbsp;
a small dose of mescaline.

00:37:07.840 --> 00:37:13.680
I was aware that something odd,
but something very good, had happened.

00:37:13.680 --> 00:37:18.120
And I was on call in this busy hospital.
I went to sleep and just slept.

00:37:18.120 --> 00:37:20.520
My pager didn't go off.
I wasn't disturbed.

00:37:20.520 --> 00:37:23.320
I woke up the next morning
and I felt very relaxed indeed.

00:37:23.320 --> 00:37:27.080
The next day I had to run around London
doing all sorts of things.

00:37:27.080 --> 00:37:31.560
What I found was really quite odd.
This may sound a little cosmic.

00:37:31.560 --> 00:37:35.720
It may sound as though
I need a little anti-psychotic medication.

00:37:36.400 --> 00:37:37.520
But this is what happened.

00:37:38.680 --> 00:37:44.120
Whenever I drove anywhere,
the lights seemed to be green. I just flowed.

00:37:44.120 --> 00:37:47.880
I had to go on the underground
in London.

00:37:47.880 --> 00:37:50.560
I just seemed to walk in.
There wasn't a line to buy a ticket.

00:37:50.560 --> 00:37:52.200
I'd buy the ticket.
The train would come in.

00:37:52.200 --> 00:37:54.120
The doors were open.
I'd get on the train and go.

00:37:54.120 --> 00:37:57.920
Instead of waiting in line
and fighting through London,

00:37:57.920 --> 00:38:01.720
I seemed to be in touch
with some sort of synchronicity.

00:38:01.720 --> 00:38:05.560
Things were just flowing and effortless.

00:38:05.560 --> 00:38:09.320
I was very conscious that this was unusual.

00:38:09.320 --> 00:38:14.520
It was a strange experience for me,
because I was used to having a hassle

00:38:14.520 --> 00:38:22.400
and having to fight my way through London
to make things happen.

00:38:23.640 --> 00:38:27.160
I think we'll just pause for one second
because Shri Mataji is here

00:38:27.160 --> 00:38:31.800
and the stage is a bit dark
so she needs to lead the way over to the stage.

00:38:31.800 --> 00:38:35.320
So, I'm just going to stop
and then when she's seated I'll carry on.

00:38:48.240 --> 00:38:53.800
This cool business that was referred to
by the previous speakers,

00:38:53.800 --> 00:38:56.560
it just seemed to flow
and it made me calm down.

00:38:56.560 --> 00:39:00.200
It worked very well in conjunction
with my 12-step programme.

00:39:00.200 --> 00:39:04.120
What I was impressed with
was that there was no money involved.

00:39:04.120 --> 00:39:07.400
I didn't have to do anything strange.
I could carry on working as a doctor

00:39:07.400 --> 00:39:10.280
in a busy Western city,

00:39:10.280 --> 00:39:14.360
if I just practised this meditation
as was gently suggested to me,

00:39:14.360 --> 00:39:20.680
and did little things to help myself,
such as put my feet in warm water in the evenings.

00:39:20.680 --> 00:39:21.640
That felt pretty strange,&nbsp;

00:39:21.640 --> 00:39:23.600
sitting with my feet in a&nbsp;
bucket of warm salted water.

00:39:24.680 --> 00:39:26.440
But actually it made me feel a lot better.

00:39:27.360 --> 00:39:32.440
For me, what I really liked about it
was that this was experiential.

00:39:32.440 --> 00:39:38.840
It wasn't some academic process.
I didn't have to learn Sanskrit.

00:39:38.840 --> 00:39:44.520
I didn't have to do anything other than just
experience what was being suggested.

00:39:44.520 --> 00:39:49.360
And I gradually began to meet Shri Mataji
and go to meetings

00:39:49.360 --> 00:39:51.520
where there were large numbers of people.

00:39:51.520 --> 00:39:56.080
What really struck me about this
is that when there are large numbers of people

00:39:56.600 --> 00:40:02.000
all actually utilising this energy,
the whole thing becomes a very powerful experience

00:40:02.000 --> 00:40:06.160
because there are energies involved
that Shri Mataji will describe.

00:40:06.160 --> 00:40:11.160
When there are groups of people doing it together
there is a collective accumulation of energy

00:40:11.160 --> 00:40:13.400
and the whole thing
becomes extremely powerful.

00:40:13.400 --> 00:40:15.960
So I went to a large meeting quite early on

00:40:15.960 --> 00:40:23.240
and I came away after a couple of days
of meditation and dance programmes

00:40:23.240 --> 00:40:26.560
and theatre and things that were put on.
It was very joyful.

00:40:26.560 --> 00:40:30.200
It wasn't the sort of intense
"let's all sit down and meditate for 24 hours"

00:40:31.400 --> 00:40:35.920
experiential stuff
that I had kind of ventured into previously.

00:40:37.840 --> 00:40:39.240
It was all very joyful,

00:40:39.240 --> 00:40:43.920
and the thing that struck me was that
Shri Mataji herself is full of joy.

00:40:43.920 --> 00:40:49.720
She would be describing very complex processes
and there would be laughing and a joyfulness

00:40:49.720 --> 00:40:55.680
and an innocence and an almost childlike state
that people seemed to be in,

00:40:55.680 --> 00:40:59.640
as well as this extremely powerful experience
of the meditation.

00:40:59.640 --> 00:41:03.680
And what that meant for me was,
when I sat down after one of these meetings,

00:41:03.680 --> 00:41:07.880
I just wasn't thinking.
I felt totally calm, completely relaxed.

00:41:07.880 --> 00:41:12.360
And when I did think,
every thought I had was spot on.

00:41:12.360 --> 00:41:15.080
It was pure.
I knew it was accurate.

00:41:15.080 --> 00:41:18.080
I knew exactly what was going on
with my patients

00:41:18.080 --> 00:41:21.480
and I just had this confidence
that when I was feeling like this —

00:41:21.480 --> 00:41:25.120
which wasn't the whole time;
it did involve doing some work

00:41:25.120 --> 00:41:30.120
to achieve this state —
but when I was in that calm state,

00:41:31.560 --> 00:41:35.720
I knew that every thought I was having
was some form of pure knowledge.

00:41:35.720 --> 00:41:38.600
It was quite extraordinary.

00:41:38.600 --> 00:41:42.200
This all happened to me about 18 years ago
and since then things have evolved.

00:41:42.200 --> 00:41:45.480
I now use Sahaja Yoga
as part of my practice.

00:41:45.480 --> 00:41:47.680
I work a lot with addicts and alcoholics.

00:41:47.680 --> 00:41:50.280
We find an awful lot of people
get involved in Sahaja Yoga

00:41:50.280 --> 00:41:53.880
and their desire to use drugs,
to smoke cigarettes, to drink alcohol

00:41:53.880 --> 00:41:55.240
simply melts away.

00:41:55.240 --> 00:41:59.240
We don't do intensive counselling.
We don't give them detoxes.

00:41:59.240 --> 00:42:02.360
Some people need to go away and have detoxes,
and when they come back

00:42:02.360 --> 00:42:11.200
they find that the state of well-being
and the flow of energy,

00:42:11.200 --> 00:42:13.200
particularly when it's done collectively,&nbsp;

00:42:13.200 --> 00:42:17.800
just seems to lead people&nbsp;
into a state of well-being

00:42:17.800 --> 00:42:21.760
and leads them into a pathway
that seems to be in their own interest.

00:42:23.640 --> 00:42:26.240
So I found that my career
has come together.

00:42:26.240 --> 00:42:27.680
Life makes much more sense.

00:42:27.680 --> 00:42:32.440
It absolutely complements
everything I was heading towards anyway.

00:42:32.440 --> 00:42:35.720
It's helped with things like
one's value system.

00:42:36.360 --> 00:42:40.480
One suddenly discovers that
driving around in fast cars

00:42:40.480 --> 00:42:42.200
doesn't seem to matter quite so much&nbsp;

00:42:42.200 --> 00:42:46.000
when this is there as a way&nbsp;
of spending one's evening.

00:42:46.000 --> 00:42:50.920
So hassling around and wheeling and dealing
just didn't seem to make a whole lot of sense.

00:42:50.920 --> 00:42:55.720
So for me, and for a lot of the patients
that I've treated subsequently,

00:42:55.720 --> 00:43:00.720
I'm in no doubt that Sahaja Yoga
is based on a scientific basis

00:43:00.720 --> 00:43:04.200
and it does need to be researched,
and we need a lot more data

00:43:04.200 --> 00:43:06.840
than we're able to present tonight.

00:43:06.840 --> 00:43:09.640
It's an experiential process.
It's not academic.

00:43:09.640 --> 00:43:18.600
We actually feel physiological sensations.
We feel energy shifting around in our body,

00:43:18.600 --> 00:43:23.400
and hopefully our technology will allow us
to experience some of that this evening.

00:43:23.400 --> 00:43:28.240
Sahaja Yoga is a complete formula
both for prevention of illness,

00:43:28.240 --> 00:43:33.040
for the diagnosis of illness
and for the treatment of illness.

00:43:33.040 --> 00:43:35.440
It's also entirely free,&nbsp;

00:43:35.440 --> 00:43:37.440
and there are other forms&nbsp;
of meditation that aren't.

00:43:37.440 --> 00:43:40.600
There are other forms of meditation and healing
where people are making a lot of money

00:43:40.600 --> 00:43:45.960
out of traditional spiritual techniques.

00:43:45.960 --> 00:43:50.800
And for me, being free
and being something that wasn't forced on me,

00:43:50.800 --> 00:43:55.480
being something that's natural,
gentle and joyful is important.

00:43:55.480 --> 00:43:58.080
So ladies and gentlemen,
I now like to introduce

00:43:58.080 --> 00:44:01.120
the teacher of Sahaja Yoga,
the founder of Sahaja Yoga,

00:44:01.120 --> 00:44:07.840
the person who has evolved
and developed this form of meditation.

00:44:07.840 --> 00:44:12.320
I know you're all very pleased to welcome
Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi,

00:44:12.320 --> 00:44:26.000
who is here with us tonight.

00:44:38.520 --> 00:44:39.520
---

00:44:39.520 --> 00:44:48.520
I bow to all the seekers of truth.

00:44:48.520 --> 00:44:55.960
At the very outset, I would like to thank
the National Institute of Health

00:44:57.720 --> 00:45:07.160
for inviting Me to speak to you people
about Sahaja Yoga.

00:45:07.160 --> 00:45:13.520
Today, I'm going to tell you
the secrets of medicine.

00:45:13.520 --> 00:45:18.840
So far whatever we have known
in the medical colleges,

00:45:21.880 --> 00:45:25.480
there is something beyond it
which we should know

00:45:25.480 --> 00:45:41.002
and utilise our knowledge for
a great deal of advantage.

00:45:41.002 --> 00:45:42.840
'Sahaja': 'saha' means 'with'
and 'ja' is 'born'.

00:45:42.840 --> 00:45:51.640
With you is born this right
to become Self-realized.

00:45:51.640 --> 00:45:55.240
Yoga is the union
with the Divine Power.

00:45:55.240 --> 00:45:59.840
We have heard about Divine Power
in all the books and scriptures,

00:45:59.840 --> 00:46:06.920
but we have never experienced it.
We don't know if it really existed or not.

00:46:06.920 --> 00:46:13.040
But the time has come
for us to experience that.

00:46:13.040 --> 00:46:20.240
Also in the medical science we know quite
a lot about sympathetic nervous systems.

00:46:20.240 --> 00:46:26.640
But we don't know much
about the parasympathetic and its control.

00:46:26.640 --> 00:46:34.760
The secret I'm going to tell you is
how to control your parasympathetic system.

00:46:45.040 --> 00:46:55.960
It controls and balances all the activity
of the sympathetic.

00:46:55.960 --> 00:46:59.680
If I say there is a power placed&nbsp;

00:46:59.680 --> 00:47:06.000
in our triangular bone,&nbsp;
which is called the sacrum,

00:47:06.000 --> 00:47:08.920
you may doubt it.

00:47:08.920 --> 00:47:13.080
But this triangular bone is called sacrum —
it's a sacred bone.

00:47:13.080 --> 00:47:17.160
That means the Greeks knew about it,
that it's a sacred bone.

00:47:17.160 --> 00:47:23.760
In this bone is placed, in three and a half coils,
that is also mathematical,

00:47:23.760 --> 00:47:30.320
three and a half coils,
a power which is made of many threads,

00:47:30.320 --> 00:47:38.560
and which is the one
we call for our ascent,

00:47:38.560 --> 00:47:43.000
for our last breakthrough.

00:47:43.000 --> 00:47:49.360
After human awareness, if we had achieved
everything in our evolution,

00:47:49.360 --> 00:47:52.200
there would have been
not all these problems.

00:47:52.200 --> 00:47:58.480
So many problems exist —
on individual level, on collective level.

00:48:00.880 --> 00:48:04.680
Why these problems should be there
if we are really fully evolved?

00:48:04.680 --> 00:48:07.031
But we are not.

00:48:07.031 --> 00:48:12.480
There is something that has to be happening,
and for that our Creator Himself

00:48:12.480 --> 00:48:16.800
has placed this power
in our triangular bone.

00:48:16.800 --> 00:48:25.440
Now you need not take my talk as granted,
but you should experiment.

00:48:25.440 --> 00:48:29.800
As honest people, you must experiment
and see for yourself

00:48:29.800 --> 00:48:36.520
if there is this power or not,
if it works or not, does it ascend or not?

00:48:38.080 --> 00:48:43.480
It's absolutely scientific.
Absolutely scientific.

00:48:43.480 --> 00:48:50.200
And once you enter into that arena
of secret science,

00:48:50.200 --> 00:48:55.760
then you'll be amazed
that there is so much to be known about ourselves.

00:48:55.760 --> 00:49:00.920
All the scriptures have said
that you should know yourself.

00:49:00.920 --> 00:49:07.200
For us, it is some separate subject,
not for doctors —

00:49:07.200 --> 00:49:17.080
some sort of a religious subject
that we should know ourselves.

00:49:20.520 --> 00:49:24.240
But now, we are going towards unity.

00:49:24.240 --> 00:49:33.400
Unity as a human being,
unity as all the religions, all the world.

00:49:33.400 --> 00:49:35.040
How do we do that?

00:49:35.040 --> 00:49:42.520
Is there any way of connecting you
to that area of Divine Power

00:49:42.520 --> 00:49:45.960
by which you all become one?

00:49:59.400 --> 00:50:09.800
The new future medical science
has to understand what is parasympathetic,

00:50:09.800 --> 00:50:15.160
what is this Kundalini I am talking about,
what is the function of this Kundalini,

00:50:15.160 --> 00:50:17.120
how it works.

00:50:17.120 --> 00:50:28.240
Now it is like a primule in a seed
which sprouts and then grows into a tree.

00:50:28.240 --> 00:50:32.360
Firstly, whatever is your seeking —
if you have not known yourself,

00:50:32.360 --> 00:50:39.240
seeking may go on and is going on
in this country like a mad race.

00:50:39.240 --> 00:50:43.280
All your seeking must come to an end,
otherwise, it has no meaning.

00:50:43.280 --> 00:50:54.600
Waste of life, waste of energy.
It's a very, very simple thing.

00:50:54.600 --> 00:51:00.280
Within you lies this power,
whatever may be your colour,

00:51:00.280 --> 00:51:03.880
whatever may be your nationality,
your religion or whatever,

00:51:03.880 --> 00:51:07.720
as long as you are a human being,
this Kundalini is there,

00:51:07.720 --> 00:51:11.789
quite ready to be ascending.

00:51:11.789 --> 00:51:18.160
It ascends automatically,
just like a seed has a primule which ascends.

00:51:18.160 --> 00:51:21.320
You don't do anything.
You don't have to stand on your head.

00:51:22.760 --> 00:51:25.840
It is there.
'Sahaj' also means spontaneous.

00:51:25.840 --> 00:51:27.760
It works out spontaneously.

00:51:27.760 --> 00:51:31.797
You all have this power within you
and only thing you have to do

00:51:31.797 --> 00:51:33.880
is experience this.

00:51:33.880 --> 00:51:41.040
This rises, this power rises,
passes through six centres,

00:51:41.040 --> 00:51:43.000
I think they have shown them here,

00:51:43.000 --> 00:51:48.840
and pierces through your fontanel bone area,
which you know what it is, I need not tell you.

00:51:48.840 --> 00:51:55.360
And then pierces through and becomes one
with this All-pervading Power.

00:51:56.040 --> 00:52:02.080
As this instrument is connected,
you also get connected.

00:52:02.080 --> 00:52:05.680
Without connection this has no meaning.

00:52:05.680 --> 00:52:10.240
In the same way we do have no meaning,
we are going here, there, there, there.

00:52:10.240 --> 00:52:14.800
But we are not yet knowing the truth,
and the truth is

00:52:14.800 --> 00:52:19.160
that you are all going to be the Spirit.

00:52:19.160 --> 00:52:24.240
Now here we come very close
to spirituality and to the eternal.

00:52:24.240 --> 00:52:30.640
Not to be afraid of it.
It is a part of us.

00:52:39.000 --> 00:52:43.720
Of course it is not mentioned
in anatomy or in any one of the books,

00:52:45.000 --> 00:52:49.120
but it is a fact.
You have to see for yourself.

00:52:49.120 --> 00:52:59.640
Don't deny because it was not in your books,
but try to see for yourself if it is so.

00:52:59.640 --> 00:53:02.880
Because how beneficial it is.

00:53:02.880 --> 00:53:08.800
First of all, all these centres
are responsible for your physical,

00:53:08.800 --> 00:53:14.000
mental, emotional
and spiritual beings.

00:53:32.960 --> 00:53:44.754
Then the right side is the knowledge
of the body and also the mental self,

00:53:44.754 --> 00:53:50.560
which is also not good.
What you know is outside, superficial.

00:53:50.560 --> 00:53:55.160
For that, what you have to do is first of all
get your Realisation.

00:53:55.960 --> 00:53:57.680
That, at least, you should have.

00:53:57.680 --> 00:54:02.240
Nothing happens to you and there is
nothing to be frightened about it.

00:54:02.240 --> 00:54:04.280
There is nothing to doubt about it.

00:54:04.280 --> 00:54:09.120
You all have to have your Self-realization —
that is the Self-knowledge.

00:54:09.120 --> 00:54:13.200
Once you have your Self-knowledge,
you know all about your chakras.

00:54:13.200 --> 00:54:17.320
On your fingertips you can feel
what's the problem with you,

00:54:17.320 --> 00:54:19.400
what's the problem of another person.

00:54:19.400 --> 00:54:22.640
For example, somebody has cancer.

00:54:22.640 --> 00:54:30.600
Now they have to go through
such a lot of treatment.

00:54:32.920 --> 00:54:38.040
But it's only on your fingertips you can say
what disease the person has.

00:54:38.040 --> 00:54:40.520
On the fingertips.

00:54:40.520 --> 00:54:43.880
Because you are entitled, you are empowered.

00:54:43.880 --> 00:54:47.836
But first raise your powers
and become that —

00:54:47.836 --> 00:54:51.160
and I'm talking about becoming
and nothing else.

00:54:51.160 --> 00:54:55.560
Unless and until you become that,
you won't understand

00:54:55.560 --> 00:55:00.120
what is the gift of the Divine to us.

00:55:00.120 --> 00:55:06.120
Once this Kundalini rises,
she enlightens all the centres.

00:55:06.120 --> 00:55:10.760
She integrates all the centres.

00:55:10.760 --> 00:55:14.040
Apart from that,
she looks after all these centres.

00:55:14.040 --> 00:55:16.880
For example, I will give you
a case of cancer.

00:55:21.520 --> 00:55:28.440
Now what we know about cancer
is different doctors for different things.

00:55:29.440 --> 00:55:32.600
But it's very simple.

00:55:35.720 --> 00:55:44.800
You have the left side and right side
of the sympathetic nervous system.

00:55:46.200 --> 00:55:48.800
Now I don't know in medicine
how far they have gone,

00:55:48.800 --> 00:55:51.760
but when I studied,
they thought both are just the same.

00:55:51.760 --> 00:55:55.000
They are not.
They are two different systems.

00:55:55.680 --> 00:56:00.440
One works for the other,
but in a way it is the opposite.

00:56:00.440 --> 00:56:02.840
So it's complementary.

00:56:02.840 --> 00:56:05.840
I'll show you now.
Supposing in my hand — I'll show you.

00:56:05.840 --> 00:56:10.840
This is one centre from the right side,
another centre from the left side,

00:56:10.840 --> 00:56:15.840
and you put them together.
Now this is the spinal cord, say for example.

00:56:15.840 --> 00:56:23.960
Now when you work very hard,
you are working your right sympathetic very much

00:56:23.960 --> 00:56:28.920
and you are exhausting your energy
in the centre, whatever it is.

00:56:28.920 --> 00:56:34.040
Suddenly your left side just breaks. Why?

00:56:34.040 --> 00:56:37.000
Maybe some shock,
maybe some accident,

00:56:37.000 --> 00:56:40.640
maybe something due to sickness.
It breaks.

00:56:40.640 --> 00:56:45.400
It breaks means it has no connection
with the centre.

00:56:45.400 --> 00:56:50.560
That means it is on its own.
That's how a malignant cell starts.

00:56:50.560 --> 00:56:52.320
Very simple as that.

00:56:52.320 --> 00:56:58.520
Now supposing by any chance
you could raise the Kundalini

00:56:58.520 --> 00:57:04.480
and push it through both these ends,
then they can look after.

00:57:04.480 --> 00:57:06.880
That's how cancer can be cured.

00:57:06.880 --> 00:57:11.840
Of course, Sahaja Yoga has cured cancer.
All kinds of cancers it has cured.

00:57:11.840 --> 00:57:18.920
But we don't want to become doctors, you see.
We don't want to do the doctor's job.

00:57:18.920 --> 00:57:24.480
But we can tell you
how you can cure so many people.

00:57:31.640 --> 00:57:40.926
So because in a short time
I can't tell you everything,

00:57:40.926 --> 00:57:40.955
let me tell about one chakra.

00:57:40.955 --> 00:57:43.246
It's the Swadisthana — they'll show you.
It's the second chakra in you.

00:57:43.246 --> 00:57:49.360
A chakra is a centre — a subtle centre
which comes out of your third centre,

00:57:49.360 --> 00:57:52.800
that we call as Nabhi chakra.

00:57:52.800 --> 00:57:58.360
And it starts moving like a lotus all over.

00:57:58.360 --> 00:58:05.400
This is the one which looks after
all the organs in the stomach.

00:58:05.400 --> 00:58:07.720
This chakra is a subtle one.

00:58:07.720 --> 00:58:11.680
Of course you may not see it in dissection,
but it is there.

00:58:11.680 --> 00:58:22.440
Now when it starts moving like this,
what happens is that you get too much on one side.

00:58:22.440 --> 00:58:24.840
Supposing you are working very hard,&nbsp;

00:58:24.840 --> 00:58:29.520
then it has to work too hard&nbsp;
if you are thinking too much.

00:58:29.520 --> 00:58:36.880
We never think how our brain is given energy,
from where does it get energy.

00:58:36.880 --> 00:58:39.065
It is through this centre
that our brain gets the energy.

00:58:39.065 --> 00:58:47.760
The grey cells get the energy
from this centre.

00:58:47.760 --> 00:58:53.760
Now this centre is working very hard
when we start thinking too much.

00:58:53.760 --> 00:58:58.280
People who think, think, think, think —
what happens is

00:59:06.480 --> 00:59:11.796
this Swadisthana chakra becomes attentive
only to the brain.

00:59:11.796 --> 00:59:20.520
But it also looks after your liver.
It looks after the pancreas.

00:59:20.520 --> 00:59:28.640
It looks after your spleen, kidneys
and also the lower intestines.

00:59:28.640 --> 00:59:30.160
That's the job
this one centre has to do.

00:59:32.320 --> 00:59:35.880
Now when you think too much,
the first thing that can happen

00:59:35.880 --> 00:59:42.040
is something goes wrong
with your liver.

00:59:42.040 --> 00:59:47.200
The liver, as you know,
is to take out all the heat of the body

00:59:49.040 --> 00:59:54.640
and deliver it into the circulation of blood.

00:59:56.400 --> 01:00:02.040
Now if that heat accumulates
it cannot do it, because the liver is failing.

01:00:02.040 --> 01:00:06.320
As a result this heat starts moving upward.

01:00:06.320 --> 01:00:09.437
Now this is not in the medical books,
but I am just telling.

01:00:09.437 --> 01:00:11.720
It starts moving upward.

01:00:11.720 --> 01:00:16.720
According to us, there is a centre
we call the right heart —

01:00:16.720 --> 01:00:19.400
a very important centre.

01:00:19.400 --> 01:00:22.040
There are three hearts:
left heart, right heart, centre of the heart.

01:00:23.800 --> 01:00:30.320
The right heart gets affected
and you can get asthma.

01:00:30.320 --> 01:00:36.000
Asthma is absolutely curable,
100% curable.

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:41.280
No doubt, but you have to take to Sahaja Yoga.
That's all.

01:00:41.280 --> 01:00:45.760
Then this heat moves from here
and goes to the heart.

01:00:45.760 --> 01:00:49.600
When a boy is young,
twenty-one or twenty-two years of age,

01:00:49.600 --> 01:00:53.920
he is playing tennis
and also drinking too much,

01:00:53.920 --> 01:00:58.600
then what happens is his liver
goes out completely,

01:00:58.600 --> 01:01:03.000
and maybe he gets such a massive heart attack
that it is fatal.

01:01:05.400 --> 01:01:12.680
But this process goes on and sometimes
people get a massive heart attack later on.

01:01:12.680 --> 01:01:23.690
So this is the heat process
which goes from here and moves to the pancreas.

01:01:23.690 --> 01:01:28.920
You get the pancreas affected,
you get diabetes.

01:01:28.920 --> 01:01:32.920
Diabetes is also curable.

01:01:34.560 --> 01:01:42.960
Then it moves down to the kidneys
and the kidneys stop.

01:01:42.960 --> 01:01:45.240
One chakra!

01:01:45.240 --> 01:01:49.360
Then heat also, as I told,
goes to the spleen.

01:01:49.360 --> 01:01:56.280
If the heat goes to the spleen,
only then you get what we call blood cancer.

01:01:56.280 --> 01:02:01.880
I shouldn't say, but we have cured
many blood cancer patients.

01:02:01.880 --> 01:02:11.160
Mostly architects and chartered accountants
get this blood cancer.

01:02:11.160 --> 01:02:15.360
They are cured.
For the last ten years they are living well.

01:03:07.240 --> 01:03:14.800
So it's a very fast happening.
I call it a 'jet Kundalini' in modern times.

01:03:14.800 --> 01:03:17.880
And it really works.
It's surprising.

01:03:17.880 --> 01:03:24.480
Now this happening of one centre is so important.

01:03:24.480 --> 01:03:32.080
There are so many diseases which can be cured
if you can look after these centres.

01:03:32.080 --> 01:03:33.120
Except for two.

01:03:34.600 --> 01:03:48.160
One is AIDS.
Because they can be cured,

01:03:48.160 --> 01:03:53.360
but they are extremely arrogant
and think they are doing a martyrdom.

01:03:54.600 --> 01:03:59.240
How can you talk to them?
It's a big problem like that.

01:04:01.160 --> 01:04:09.320
Then another is Alzheimer's.
That's another disease you cannot attend to.

01:04:09.320 --> 01:04:14.120
Because this comes to people
who have been like Hitlers in their lifetime —

01:04:14.120 --> 01:04:18.120
arrogant, very aggressive.

01:04:18.120 --> 01:04:21.760
These people, when they get this disease,
become even worse.

01:04:21.760 --> 01:04:26.560
They may even abuse you.
They can't get up and hit you,

01:04:26.560 --> 01:04:30.200
but they will say everything
that upsets others.

01:04:30.200 --> 01:04:38.880
So you give up your hopes about them.
Not that they cannot be cured,

01:04:38.880 --> 01:04:44.360
but it's a little too much
to attend to them.

01:04:44.360 --> 01:04:48.400
I tried with three people
then I gave it up.

01:04:48.400 --> 01:04:49.800
When they started abusing Me&nbsp;

01:04:52.440 --> 01:04:56.520
I was surprised they couldn't&nbsp;
receive any vibrations.

01:04:56.520 --> 01:04:58.960
So I said, "This cannot work out".

01:04:58.960 --> 01:05:01.520
So one has to be humble about it.

01:05:01.520 --> 01:05:06.080
If you think you have known everything,
it won't work out.

01:05:06.080 --> 01:05:09.160
Another thing, you have to be
extremely honest.

01:05:09.160 --> 01:05:16.120
You have to be honest to yourself
and honest to the knowledge of Sahaja Yoga.

01:05:16.120 --> 01:05:21.400
It's all for you, absolutely free.
It's the best that can happen.

01:05:21.400 --> 01:05:26.440
Now I was told that in this institution
you have a lot of research happening.

01:05:26.440 --> 01:05:30.440
I would love you people
to do this research on Sahaja Yoga.

01:05:30.440 --> 01:05:31.720
All of you.

01:05:31.720 --> 01:05:38.680
All the rest of the gimmicks people have done —
they were not at all scientific, in no way.

01:05:38.680 --> 01:05:42.080
For this, you don't have to do much research,

01:05:42.080 --> 01:05:46.640
because you raise the Kundalini
of one person and you will see the results.

01:05:46.640 --> 01:05:49.360
It's a tremendous power within you.

01:05:49.360 --> 01:05:51.240
But we don't know our value.

01:05:51.240 --> 01:05:53.520
That's what they said:
"You should know your Self."

01:05:53.520 --> 01:06:00.400
We don't know what we have,
what powers we have, what we can do.

01:06:00.400 --> 01:06:04.560
Not through book knowledge,
but through the knowledge of the Divine.

01:06:04.560 --> 01:06:12.920
So when we come to that,
we understand that spirituality and good health,

01:06:12.920 --> 01:06:14.920
everything is to be proved.

01:06:14.920 --> 01:06:16.920
So as a result,
what do you get?

01:06:16.920 --> 01:06:21.920
On your fingertips, you can feel the centres.

01:06:21.920 --> 01:06:26.454
Five, six and seven
on the left sympathetic.

01:06:26.454 --> 01:06:27.840
Five, six and seven
on the right sympathetic.

01:06:27.840 --> 01:06:30.400
You can feel it,
where is the problem.

01:06:30.400 --> 01:06:37.520
Then no need to take tests —
on the fingertips you can see where the problem is

01:06:37.520 --> 01:06:39.480
and what should be attended to.

01:06:39.480 --> 01:06:42.680
It's a simple method of doing it.

01:06:59.640 --> 01:07:03.560
Like so many people have suggested
and have written books

01:07:03.560 --> 01:07:07.040
that if the Kundalini rises,
then this problem comes and that.

01:07:07.040 --> 01:07:08.400
Nothing of the kind.

01:07:08.400 --> 01:07:14.480
Last thirty years I have been doing this.
I have not seen one person anything&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:07:14.480 --> 01:07:15.360
happening to him.

01:07:15.360 --> 01:07:16.800
Never, never.

01:07:16.800 --> 01:07:23.160
So it is for you just to see,
spend at the most one month.

01:07:23.160 --> 01:07:25.400
And you will be amazed.
You will be masters.

01:07:26.800 --> 01:07:31.880
Because it's your own power.
It is not somebody else's power.

01:07:31.880 --> 01:07:33.120
It's your own power.

01:07:33.120 --> 01:07:34.880
Only thing — you should have&nbsp;

01:07:34.880 --> 01:07:42.840
the full knowledge about the&nbsp;
secret science of medicine.

01:07:42.840 --> 01:07:45.720
Because with this we have therapy.

01:07:45.720 --> 01:07:51.040
Medicine is for curing people and health.
Then this is the best, easiest way.

01:07:51.040 --> 01:07:52.960
But that doesn't mean you discard.

01:07:52.960 --> 01:07:57.040
Because you are much more knowledgeable about it,
you know what the problem is.

01:07:57.040 --> 01:08:01.880
With the symptoms also you can say
and you can verify. Very easily.

01:08:03.080 --> 01:08:12.240
Supposing you put your hands to something
and you feel that person is a psychological case.

01:08:12.240 --> 01:08:14.280
You find out, you verify.

01:08:14.280 --> 01:08:19.000
And psychological cases
are completely cured in Sahaja Yoga.

01:08:19.000 --> 01:08:23.040
There is one patient here
who was with you.

01:08:23.560 --> 01:08:29.160
Only, I think two years back I met him.
And today he is a cured man.

01:08:29.160 --> 01:08:33.520
Psychology is very difficult,
I must say, I'm sorry.

01:08:33.520 --> 01:08:39.080
But they think it's very hard to cure.

01:08:39.080 --> 01:08:43.920
Also, medically affected people
can also be very cured.

01:08:43.920 --> 01:08:46.080
First, you must become the masters.

01:08:46.080 --> 01:08:48.560
You must have the whole powers within.

01:08:48.560 --> 01:08:52.440
And then you work it out,
and you will be amazed

01:08:52.440 --> 01:08:57.880
what powers you have,
how much you can do to help this world.

01:08:57.880 --> 01:09:00.560
Apart from that, the best thing&nbsp;

01:09:00.560 --> 01:09:04.960
that happens is a person&nbsp;
gets completely transformed.

01:09:04.960 --> 01:09:12.920
I feel, I have written also in my book,
that in the genes we have a phosphorus.

01:09:12.920 --> 01:09:17.600
And if a person is dry, less water,
this phosphorus explodes

01:09:17.600 --> 01:09:20.320
and you get into tempers.

01:09:20.320 --> 01:09:30.720
Getting into tempers is not your doing —
it's just this phosphorus working out the heat.

01:09:59.080 --> 01:10:03.080
So you get your experience.
Then you get your peace.

01:10:03.080 --> 01:10:04.120
How to get your peace?

01:10:04.120 --> 01:10:12.880
It's very simple that our style is
we see anything, we react.

01:10:13.600 --> 01:10:19.520
I see this top table, I react.
I see people, I react.

01:10:19.520 --> 01:10:22.320
But with Kundalini rising, it stops.

01:10:22.320 --> 01:10:29.720
How? Because a thought arises, falls down,
and a thought arises, falls down.

01:10:29.720 --> 01:10:35.760
It's a continuous thing and we are mostly
jumping on the cusps of these thoughts.

01:10:35.760 --> 01:10:41.520
Now when the Kundalini rises,
she elongates those thoughts.

01:10:41.520 --> 01:10:45.157
There is a space in between —
it's called in Sanskrit, the 'villamba'.

01:10:45.157 --> 01:10:47.240
We can call it pause.

01:10:47.240 --> 01:10:53.800
And when your mind stops like that,
you become thoughtlessly aware.

01:10:53.800 --> 01:10:57.600
You are thoughtless
but you are extremely aware,

01:10:57.600 --> 01:10:59.840
and you reach the witness state.

01:10:59.840 --> 01:11:03.480
You see everything as a witness.
Just as a witness.

01:11:03.480 --> 01:11:07.680
Say for example, I see a beautiful carpet.

01:11:07.680 --> 01:11:14.640
I am very much enamoured and I react:
"Oh my God, what a good carpet!

01:11:14.640 --> 01:11:16.960
How much it must have cost?
Where can I get it?"

01:11:17.680 --> 01:11:19.600
Supposing it's mine,
then I am too worried:

01:11:19.600 --> 01:11:23.760
"I have not yet registered it
or insured it, so there is a problem."

01:11:23.760 --> 01:11:29.520
But supposing I am a Realised soul,
then I just watch it.

01:11:29.520 --> 01:11:35.720
I watch it silently and enjoy
all the art that is put into it.

01:11:35.720 --> 01:11:40.000
That's how you learn how to enjoy art.

01:11:40.000 --> 01:11:43.180
In Sahaja Yoga, I've known people
who were chartered accountants

01:11:43.180 --> 01:11:46.760
who never knew anything
about music or poetry

01:11:46.760 --> 01:11:50.480
and have become very great poets.

01:11:50.480 --> 01:11:52.760
Somebody who never used to sing
has started singing.

01:11:52.760 --> 01:11:54.720
So many things have happened.

01:11:54.720 --> 01:12:02.360
Apart from that, anything —
I must tell in this country — that you prosper.

01:12:02.360 --> 01:12:06.680
Because your awareness is so great
that you prosper.

01:12:06.680 --> 01:12:12.960
All those Sahaja Yogis
who have come to Sahaja Yoga have prospered.

01:12:12.960 --> 01:12:18.120
Not that you are hankering after money.
But money hankers after you.

01:12:19.640 --> 01:12:23.480
Why? Because your attention is so deft,
your attention is so pure,

01:12:24.720 --> 01:12:29.000
in the light of the Spirit,
your attention knows

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:32.760
what is destructive for you,
what is constructive for you.

01:12:32.760 --> 01:12:37.540
For example, somebody gets the money
and goes on wasting on this and that,

01:12:37.540 --> 01:12:42.960
getting all the bad qualities
that are not needed for body or mind.

01:12:42.960 --> 01:12:49.320
But supposing he is a Realised soul,
he gets the money.

01:12:49.320 --> 01:12:55.840
He says, "It's there for some good purpose."
And that's how he works it out.

01:12:55.840 --> 01:13:01.520
So the prosperity comes, and the joy.

01:13:01.520 --> 01:13:06.520
Joy is singular.
It is not happiness or unhappiness.

01:13:06.520 --> 01:13:14.520
If you feel joyous, you feel so joyous
and happy and you don't hurt anybody.

01:13:16.200 --> 01:13:21.600
You just enjoy your compassion,
your love, your confidence.

01:13:21.600 --> 01:13:25.080
So this is what, when we were students,
we used to think:

01:13:25.720 --> 01:13:29.400
for expression of our love,
we have become a doctor.

01:13:29.400 --> 01:13:31.680
For our compassion,
we have become a doctor.

01:13:31.680 --> 01:13:34.600
But now the ideology has changed.

01:13:35.640 --> 01:13:38.360
You enjoy your work.

01:13:38.360 --> 01:13:40.520
I mean, I'm not paying any money
to these doctors,

01:13:40.520 --> 01:13:44.880
neither are they trying
to get money from the patients.

01:13:44.880 --> 01:13:51.320
But the enjoyment of curing is so great —
much greater than all the wealth of the world.

01:13:51.320 --> 01:13:54.600
And that's how you get it.
But you don't become poor.

01:13:54.600 --> 01:14:10.360
There are so many ways you are helped,
because this Divine Power is all-pervading.

01:14:19.080 --> 01:14:23.280
That's how you understand
how to have your beautiful family,

01:14:23.920 --> 01:14:27.440
how to have your beautiful
relationships with each other,

01:14:27.440 --> 01:14:34.680
how to lead a very beautiful life
and make a beautiful country.

01:14:34.680 --> 01:14:37.240
Such people are needed today.

01:14:37.240 --> 01:14:45.480
Such happy, joyous, peaceful
and loving people we need.

01:14:45.480 --> 01:14:49.956
And that you get —
for that you don't have to suffer in any way.

01:14:49.956 --> 01:14:52.040
You don't have to suffer.
You enjoy.

01:14:52.040 --> 01:14:57.320
For curing others, you don't suffer.
You really enjoy every bit of it.

01:14:57.320 --> 01:15:00.040
So I wish you all the best of luck.

01:15:00.040 --> 01:15:07.560
Please, if you want to have Self-realization,
we'll work it out today.

01:15:07.560 --> 01:15:14.400
But that's not the end of it.
You have to attend our centres.

01:15:14.400 --> 01:15:18.200
No money in it.
You can't pay any money.

01:15:18.200 --> 01:15:19.920
This is one thing you should know.

01:15:19.920 --> 01:15:23.200
In this country, they could not accept Me
because I was not taking any money.

01:15:23.200 --> 01:15:23.231
Can you believe that?

01:15:23.231 --> 01:15:30.071
They said, "You have no Rolls Royce?"
I said, "No. I have only one car, my husband has."

01:15:30.071 --> 01:15:31.920
"You are in the business?"
"No, I'm not."

01:15:31.920 --> 01:15:34.560
"Then we don't want you."

01:15:34.560 --> 01:15:37.480
This attitude has to change.

01:15:37.480 --> 01:15:38.880
What will you ask for?

01:15:38.880 --> 01:15:43.480
For joy, for happiness,
for doing good to others.

01:15:43.480 --> 01:15:50.040
And automatically your heart starts melting
and really you become a wonderful person.

01:15:50.040 --> 01:15:52.000
Other problems also get solved.

01:15:52.000 --> 01:15:57.560
Like, too much of right side —
because I'm saying, because you are doctors —

01:15:57.560 --> 01:16:01.640
you people all develop right side more
than the left side.

01:16:01.640 --> 01:16:05.320
Another thing which is very dangerous
that one can get into

01:16:05.320 --> 01:16:09.000
is the same heat going into your head.

01:16:09.000 --> 01:16:18.480
So you can get paraplegia.
It's common. It's very, very common.

01:16:18.480 --> 01:16:20.657
But that's not necessary.

01:16:20.657 --> 01:16:23.120
Now you know, I'm very old,
much older than all of you.

01:16:23.920 --> 01:16:31.080
But one thing is there —
I'm very active and I never feel tired.

01:16:31.080 --> 01:16:40.000
It's so enjoyable, the whole thing is,
to talk to people about it.

01:16:40.000 --> 01:16:45.240
Moreover, it cannot be forced on you.
It cannot.

01:16:45.240 --> 01:16:52.000
You have to ask.
Why? Because this Kundalini is the pure desire.

01:16:52.000 --> 01:16:56.040
You know one thing —
that our desires are not satiable.

01:16:56.040 --> 01:16:59.280
If they were pure,
there would have been no economics.

01:16:59.280 --> 01:17:02.240
Because you want to have one thing,
all right, you get it.

01:17:02.240 --> 01:17:06.880
Then you want to have another thing,
you get it. You are never satisfied.

01:17:06.880 --> 01:17:12.800
So when this pure desire ascends,
you get the satisfaction.

01:17:12.800 --> 01:17:22.670
And that is why you enjoy each and everything.
That's the temperament you should develop.

01:17:22.670 --> 01:17:22.680
Beautiful.

01:17:22.680 --> 01:17:25.320
Human beings are very beautiful.

01:17:25.320 --> 01:17:30.080
I think they are a little bit lost
in the wilderness.

01:17:30.080 --> 01:17:35.760
And they have to come back
to understanding of the truth.

01:17:35.760 --> 01:17:40.680
Because you get the absolute truth.
Absolute truth.

01:17:40.680 --> 01:17:43.760
If any person comes to Me,
I see into my hands.

01:17:43.760 --> 01:17:45.800
I say, "Here it is."

01:17:45.800 --> 01:17:48.480
You can verify the absolute truth.

01:17:48.480 --> 01:17:57.120
Any person who comes and tries to cheat you
as a guru — you can easily find out

01:17:57.120 --> 01:18:00.560
if they're true or not.

01:18:00.560 --> 01:18:07.200
Any other thing, whatever you want to know,
it is absolute knowledge that you can get.

01:18:07.200 --> 01:18:13.400
We call it 'Gyana' —
it means the power of knowledge

01:18:13.400 --> 01:18:15.880
and the power of absolute knowledge.

01:18:15.880 --> 01:18:22.800
On your nervous system you feel it.
It's very, very dynamic.

01:18:22.800 --> 01:18:24.880
But you are dynamic.

01:18:24.880 --> 01:18:28.000
It's still — it's a sleeping Kundalini.

01:18:28.000 --> 01:18:31.040
Let it rise and you will see
how dynamic you are,

01:18:31.040 --> 01:18:35.080
how much you are effective,
how much you can work it out.

01:18:35.080 --> 01:18:43.240
Thank you very much again
and I would request people to understand

01:18:43.240 --> 01:18:47.880
that I cannot force it on you.
It has to be of your desire.

01:18:47.880 --> 01:18:53.800
And so, I would say,
if you don't want to have your Self-realization,

01:18:53.800 --> 01:18:55.080
then go away.

01:18:55.080 --> 01:18:57.000
But it's nothing —
it hardly takes ten&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:18:57.000 --> 01:19:00.240
minutes for you to reach the heavens.

01:19:00.240 --> 01:19:22.840
So why not try it?

01:19:24.880 --> 01:19:25.880
---

01:19:25.880 --> 01:19:35.960
I wonder if you could be specific
about what one would expect to see

01:19:35.960 --> 01:19:38.440
if somebody sits.

01:19:38.440 --> 01:19:42.800
Does one sit in that position?
Does one say a mantra?

01:19:42.800 --> 01:19:48.160
Does one do physical movement?
Does one close one's eyes?

01:19:49.360 --> 01:19:52.840
I have no idea what you are talking about.

01:20:01.680 --> 01:20:03.600
That I will tell you, definitely.

01:20:03.600 --> 01:20:06.276
But you don't have to stand on your head,
nothing of the kind.

01:20:06.276 --> 01:20:07.480
All right? It's very simple.

01:20:07.480 --> 01:20:16.069
Wherever you are sitting, it's all right.
Thank you for asking.

01:20:16.069 --> 01:20:16.072
---

01:20:16.072 --> 01:20:22.760
Mataji, what would be the effect
of diet and posture on meditation?

01:20:22.760 --> 01:20:31.720
This you can find out.

01:20:31.720 --> 01:20:33.040
Once you have your Realisation,&nbsp;

01:20:33.040 --> 01:20:36.760
you will realize what sort&nbsp;
of a personality you are

01:20:36.760 --> 01:20:39.600
and what sort of food you should have.

01:20:45.320 --> 01:20:49.080
Once you get your Realisation,
you yourself will realize

01:20:49.080 --> 01:20:52.720
what kind of food you should take
and what kind of posture you should do.

01:20:55.040 --> 01:21:04.140
Certain schools say that the kind of diet
you take — say fruits and natural foods —

01:21:04.140 --> 01:21:07.960
will provide an aid in meditating properly.

01:21:08.520 --> 01:21:25.520
Things like meat or wine,
they say, will not work properly.

01:21:25.520 --> 01:21:31.520
It's not like that.
It's a very analytical thing.

01:21:31.520 --> 01:21:36.080
Say for example, I would say in general,
in India, people should eat meat

01:21:36.080 --> 01:21:40.200
because they are so weak,
their muscles are so weak.

01:21:40.200 --> 01:21:46.400
But say in the European countries,
they should eat less meat

01:21:46.400 --> 01:21:49.072
because they are quite muscular,
I think sometimes.

01:21:49.072 --> 01:21:56.868
But for a liver patient,
there is another kind of food.

01:21:56.868 --> 01:22:03.000
You see, it depends on the personality.
All right?

01:22:16.880 --> 01:22:17.880
---

01:22:17.880 --> 01:22:22.560
My son is autistic
and he has a very low mental IQ.

01:22:23.240 --> 01:22:52.560
So how can I treat him?
How can he do the yoga?

01:22:52.560 --> 01:23:05.480
He can be cured.
He can be cured.

01:23:05.480 --> 01:23:08.543
Where is your meditation class
and how can we get there?

01:23:08.543 --> 01:23:10.760
No, no, you have to come
and we will see.

01:23:10.760 --> 01:23:16.640
We can try
and you don't have to pay anything.

01:23:16.640 --> 01:24:04.397
You bring that son there,
your child, and you see for yourself.

01:24:04.397 --> 01:24:04.400
---

01:24:04.400 --> 01:24:11.000
She is talking about somebody
who is 29 years of age and he can't even sit.

01:24:11.000 --> 01:24:14.440
So I said, "All right,
you get your Realisation.

01:24:14.440 --> 01:24:16.920
You understand
and you can cure him."

01:24:16.920 --> 01:24:19.360
Also, these people can go and do it.

01:24:21.160 --> 01:24:22.360
She can do it herself.

01:24:24.360 --> 01:24:27.640
We have no hospital here, nothing.

01:24:27.640 --> 01:24:32.120
I wanted one of these doctors
to come and stay here

01:24:32.120 --> 01:24:35.800
and tell you about Sahaja Yoga.

01:24:37.040 --> 01:24:41.840
If somebody could be employed or something,
he could come here.

01:24:41.840 --> 01:24:45.040
That was my suggestion.

01:25:04.600 --> 01:25:05.600
---

01:25:05.600 --> 01:25:13.387
This is about Sahaja Yoga.
So you are dealing with the Kundalini yoga here.

01:25:13.387 --> 01:25:31.800
In India and everywhere.
It's not here only.

01:25:46.400 --> 01:25:49.360
All right. That's the point for that.

01:25:49.360 --> 01:25:51.480
You have to come to our centre.

01:25:51.480 --> 01:25:56.480
We have got books.
I have written four books, I think.

01:25:56.480 --> 01:26:00.440
And also we have written about medicine.
You can come and get it.

01:26:00.440 --> 01:26:03.840
They will help you.
But you have to come there, you see?

01:26:03.840 --> 01:26:08.280
Yes, I will come there.
But is there some flyer?

01:26:08.280 --> 01:26:13.840
Can you let us know
where the yoga centres are here in Maryland?

01:26:17.520 --> 01:26:20.120
That information will be conveyed
to you shortly.

01:26:24.320 --> 01:26:27.040
They will do all that
and tell you where things are.

01:26:27.040 --> 01:26:29.920
Now, most of them are anxious
to get their Self-realization.

01:26:29.920 --> 01:26:34.040
So you get your Self-realization,
and then you go to the centre also.

01:26:34.040 --> 01:26:37.360
All right? Thank you.

01:26:50.840 --> 01:26:51.840
---

01:26:51.840 --> 01:26:56.920
I have worked with the AIDS patients
that you mentioned

01:26:56.920 --> 01:27:03.120
and they want to come back to the meetings
and they do the meditation themselves.

01:27:03.120 --> 01:27:07.400
They have been treating themselves.

01:27:13.800 --> 01:27:19.760
All these things you can ask
at the centre.

01:27:19.760 --> 01:27:21.200
Why not ask there?

01:27:21.200 --> 01:27:23.520
While people are waiting
to get their Self-realization.

01:27:24.440 --> 01:27:27.000
So let's respect that.

01:27:27.000 --> 01:27:52.120
We have to respect them,
respect ourselves also.

01:27:53.920 --> 01:27:54.920
---

01:27:54.920 --> 01:27:59.640
All right. Now everybody must sit down.
That's important.

01:27:59.640 --> 01:28:03.582
You should be relaxed.
Please be seated.

01:28:03.582 --> 01:28:07.100
You all should be relaxed.

01:28:07.100 --> 01:28:13.680
Now one humble thing I have to ask
is to take out your shoes

01:28:13.680 --> 01:28:16.800
because Mother Earth
will also help you.

01:29:13.600 --> 01:29:17.720
Please put both your hands towards Me,
just like this.

01:29:17.720 --> 01:29:19.320
Simple like this.

01:29:19.320 --> 01:29:29.005
If they are on your lap,
it's also all right.

01:29:29.005 --> 01:29:29.040
Whichever way you feel comfortable.

01:29:29.040 --> 01:29:36.160
Now, at the very outset,
I have to ask you one thing —

01:29:36.160 --> 01:29:40.920
that you should not feel guilty at all
for anything.

01:29:40.920 --> 01:29:43.880
I'm catching this finger,
that means there are people&nbsp;&nbsp;

01:29:43.880 --> 01:29:47.040
who are feeling guilty.

01:29:47.040 --> 01:29:51.160
Whatever has happened in the past is past.
It's finished.

01:29:51.160 --> 01:29:55.440
And the future doesn't exist.
You have to be in the present.

01:29:55.440 --> 01:29:57.520
And so please, don't feel guilty.

01:29:57.520 --> 01:30:02.000
If something has been done wrong,
all right, so what?

01:30:02.000 --> 01:30:05.520
At this moment, at least,
you should not be guilty.

01:30:05.520 --> 01:30:08.880
It's a wrong thing
to feel guilty and kill yourself.

01:30:10.280 --> 01:30:14.200
I don't know why,
in the West they have done nothing wrong.

01:30:14.200 --> 01:30:16.720
If they were guilty,
they would have been in jail.

01:30:16.720 --> 01:30:20.080
It's a common fashion
to feel guilty also.

01:30:20.080 --> 01:30:26.720
Indians will never feel guilty, somehow.
They don't know how to fight to feel guilty.

01:30:26.720 --> 01:30:31.720
And then another thing is
that you have to forgive others.

01:30:31.720 --> 01:30:33.760
Forgive others.

01:30:33.760 --> 01:30:39.303
You may say, "Mother,
it's very difficult to forgive others."

01:30:39.303 --> 01:30:39.320
You may say that.

01:30:39.320 --> 01:30:46.360
But what I would say logically is,
whether you forgive or not forgive,

01:30:50.520 --> 01:30:52.120
you are doing nothing.

01:30:52.120 --> 01:30:56.320
By not forgiving,
only you torture yourself.

01:30:56.320 --> 01:30:58.560
So forgive.

01:30:58.560 --> 01:31:03.000
Forgive everyone and forgive yourself.

01:31:03.000 --> 01:31:07.860
That's a very important thing
and it has such a tremendous power.

01:31:07.860 --> 01:31:13.840
So I request you to forgive yourself
and forgive others.

01:31:13.840 --> 01:31:14.640
That's all.

01:31:14.640 --> 01:31:21.760
If you can do this, it will work out,
and I'm sure it will work out.

01:31:24.360 --> 01:31:26.120
Now, how do you forgive?

01:31:26.120 --> 01:31:27.006
Just to say, "Mother, I forgive everyone."
That's all.

01:31:27.006 --> 01:31:31.640
"Mother, I forgive myself.
Mother, I forgive everyone."

01:31:32.880 --> 01:31:37.296
You can say that.

01:31:37.296 --> 01:31:37.320
It's very simple to say.

01:31:37.320 --> 01:31:40.600
That's not a mantra or anything,
but it's a very big thing,

01:31:40.600 --> 01:31:43.200
because it opens the centre here,
at the Agnya,

01:31:43.200 --> 01:31:47.400
which is on the crossing
of the optic chiasma, which is very constricted.

01:31:47.400 --> 01:31:51.080
And it opens like that.

01:31:51.080 --> 01:31:54.680
So just say that,
because the Kundalini has to rise.

01:31:54.680 --> 01:32:05.160
That's the main thing.

01:32:05.160 --> 01:32:10.960
Now please put your right hand towards Me
and put down your head

01:32:10.960 --> 01:32:16.160
and see for yourself if there's a cool breeze
coming out of your head.

01:32:16.160 --> 01:32:16.880
Just see.

01:32:16.880 --> 01:32:21.040
Cool or hot breeze coming out
of the fontanel bone area.

01:32:21.040 --> 01:32:22.360
Just see for yourself.

01:32:22.360 --> 01:32:28.080
You can put your hand up there,
or on the sides, forward, backward,

01:32:28.080 --> 01:32:29.520
anywhere you feel like.

01:32:29.520 --> 01:32:36.720
And see for yourself if there's a cool breeze
or hot breeze like vibrations coming out.

01:32:36.720 --> 01:32:43.240
It is hot because you have not forgiven yourself
or you have not forgiven others.

01:32:43.240 --> 01:32:44.360
This must be the reason.

01:32:44.360 --> 01:32:50.200
But let feel that it's coming out of your head —
that is the biggest proof.

01:32:50.200 --> 01:32:51.640
Now don't doubt it.

01:32:51.640 --> 01:32:55.160
There's no air conditioning in your head
that it is coming out.

01:32:55.160 --> 01:32:56.880
People start doubting like that.

01:32:56.880 --> 01:32:58.120
So raise it a little bit.

01:32:58.120 --> 01:33:00.400
Now raise it.
Not in front.

01:33:00.400 --> 01:33:14.200
Take it on the fontanel bone area
which was the soft bone in our childhood.

01:33:14.200 --> 01:33:21.720
Now please put the left hand towards Me,
and bend your head

01:33:21.720 --> 01:33:25.180
and see, with the right hand now,
see for yourself

01:33:25.180 --> 01:33:39.400
if there's a cool or a hot breeze
coming out of your head.

01:33:39.400 --> 01:33:42.800
Have faith in yourself.
That's the main thing.

01:33:42.800 --> 01:33:47.880
You all can get Realisation
and you can become Self-realised also,

01:33:47.880 --> 01:33:51.960
just like Sufis.

01:33:51.960 --> 01:34:00.180
Now put your right hand towards Me
and left hand again on the fontanel bone area.

01:34:00.180 --> 01:34:04.000
You can move your hand
and see for yourself

01:34:04.000 --> 01:34:12.440
if there's a cool or a hot breeze
coming out of your head.

01:34:12.440 --> 01:34:26.160
Now after this, please put both your hands
towards Me like that, and don't think.

01:34:26.160 --> 01:34:38.760
Just don't think.
Don't think. Just don't think.

01:34:38.760 --> 01:34:51.480
Have your hands fully open like this
and don't think.

01:34:53.880 --> 01:35:04.080
All those who have felt cool or hot breeze
on the fingertips, or on the palm,

01:35:04.080 --> 01:35:12.280
or on top of your head,
out of the fontanel bone area,

01:35:12.280 --> 01:35:18.960
please raise your hands.

01:35:18.960 --> 01:35:28.920
Oh My God! Thank you very much.
So many of you, wow!

01:35:28.920 --> 01:35:34.840
Now I have a very humble request —
that you must attend the courses in our centres.

01:35:34.840 --> 01:35:38.680
Please attend our centre
and try to master this.

01:35:39.680 --> 01:35:40.400
You can.

01:35:40.400 --> 01:35:45.720
This power that is given you here
is coming out of your fontanel bone area,

01:35:45.720 --> 01:35:48.240
and it is there.

01:35:48.240 --> 01:35:51.520
It's so great and works in no time.

01:35:51.520 --> 01:35:57.720
So I would request you to please go
to our centre and master it.

01:35:57.720 --> 01:36:03.720
And you will see how many wonders you can do,
because you are so powerful.

01:36:03.720 --> 01:36:08.385
Again I thank you very much,
all of you and your institute

01:36:08.385 --> 01:36:10.400
which has been so kind to Me.

01:36:10.400 --> 01:36:28.000
Thank you.

